"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50603","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-05-14","<p>The consultation on the future of the Energy Company Obligation (ECO) closed on 16 April 2014, and the Government expects to publish its response before Parliament rises for Summer recess.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50603/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50603/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50603/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-05-12",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what plans he has for the Energy Company Obligation; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","198423"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50604","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-05-14","<p>The Government has already confirmed that the Energy Company Obligation (ECO) is intended to be ambitious and long-term, extending through until at least 2022.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50604/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50604/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50604/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-05-12",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, if he will make it his policy to return the Energy Company Obligation to its originally announced level.","false","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","198422"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50605","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-05-14","<p>The recent consultation on the future of the Energy Company Obligation (ECO) focussed on the period between now and 2017. The precise shape of the obligation after March 2017 will be the subject of a separate consultation in due course.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50605/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50605/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50605/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-05-12",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, for what reason his Department's consultation on the Energy Company Obligation does not include a return to its originally announced level.","false","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","198421"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50606","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p>Improving outcomes for people with liver disease is a priority and tackling it is reflected in the NHS Outcomes Framework, the Public Health Outcomes Framework and in the Government's mandate to the National Health Service.</p><p> </p><p>Building on last year's ‘Call to Action', <em>Living Well for Longer: National Support for Local Action to Reduce Premature Avoidable Mortality</em> brings together the national actions which will be taken by the Department and wider Government, NHS England and Public Health England (PHE), to reduce premature mortality in England. It focuses on the five big killers including liver disease and includes a system wide delivery plan for 2014-15. This plan reflects the key actions which will be taken to reduce premature mortality taking into account the commitments that each of these organisations have made in their 2014-15 business plan. Progress against these commitments will be tracked and reported on next year.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, PHE is meeting with the All-Party Parliamentary Hepatology Group, and other stakeholders, in July to discuss the recommendations of its recent report into liver disease.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","198362","2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50606/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50606/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50606/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-12",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what response his Department plans to make to the findings and recommendations of the All-Party Parliamentary Hepatology Group's recent report into liver disease, Today's Complacency, Tomorrow's Catastrophe, published on 25 March 2014; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mike Wood","Batley and Spen","Mike Wood","198359"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50607","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p>Public Health England is currently working with NHS England and other partners to reduce the burden of disease from hepatitis C through a suite of activities to improve awareness, prevention, testing and diagnosis, referral into care, and treatment outcomes. The Department is supportive of this work, and is helping to facilitate it.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50607/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50607/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50607/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-12",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to ensure that his Department, NHS England, Public Health England, clinical commissioning groups and local authorities co-ordinate a national approach to improving the prevention, testing, diagnosis and treatment of Hepatitis C.","false","Biography information for Mike Wood","Batley and Spen","Mike Wood","198360"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50608","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p>Public Health England (PHE) is committed to working with NHS England and other partners to reduce the burden of disease from hepatitis C through a suite of activities to improve awareness, prevention, testing and diagnosis, referral into care, and treatment outcomes</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The feasibility of elimination – that is the reduction to zero of the incidence of disease or infection in England - has not been formally assessed and it is likely to be difficult in the absence of an effective vaccine. However, PHE has recently completed modelling work to assess the potential impact of increased uptake and new therapies on reducing the future burden of hepatitis C-related end stage liver disease in England. This work is being finalised and will be published shortly.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50608/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50608/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50608/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-12",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the feasibility of effectively eliminating Hepatitis C in the UK in the next 15 to 20 years.","false","Biography information for Mike Wood","Batley and Spen","Mike Wood","198361"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50609","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p>Improving outcomes for people with liver disease is a priority and tackling it is reflected in the NHS Outcomes Framework, the Public Health Outcomes Framework and in the Government's mandate to the National Health Service.</p><p> </p><p>Building on last year's ‘Call to Action', <em>Living Well for Longer: National Support for Local Action to Reduce Premature Avoidable Mortality</em> brings together the national actions which will be taken by the Department and wider Government, NHS England and Public Health England (PHE), to reduce premature mortality in England. It focuses on the five big killers including liver disease and includes a system wide delivery plan for 2014-15. This plan reflects the key actions which will be taken to reduce premature mortality taking into account the commitments that each of these organisations have made in their 2014-15 business plan. Progress against these commitments will be tracked and reported on next year.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, PHE is meeting with the All-Party Parliamentary Hepatology Group, and other stakeholders, in July to discuss the recommendations of its recent report into liver disease.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","198359","2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50609/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50609/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50609/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-12",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of progress in reducing avoidable deaths from liver disease as set out in his call to action to reduce avoidable premature mortality; and what further steps his Department will be taking.","false","Biography information for Mike Wood","Batley and Spen","Mike Wood","198362"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50611","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-05-14","<p>As of 30 April 2014, there were in total 54 Department of Energy and Climate Change jobs as part of the Licensing Exploration and Development Unit, 32 based in London, and 22 based in Aberdeen.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50611/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50611/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50611/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-05-12",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how many jobs in his Department are based in (a) London and (b) Aberdeen as part of the Licensing Exploration and Development Unit.","false","Biography information for Mike Weir","Angus","Mr Mike Weir","198410"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50616","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p>The information requested could only be obtained at a disproportionate cost.</p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50616/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50616/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50616/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-12",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people have had their permanent injury benefit reduced because of the change from sickness benefit to employment and support allowance.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","198357"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50617","Department for Transport","false","2014-05-14","<p> </p><p>The majority of public funding for local bus services is via block grant provided to local authorities in England from the Department for Communities and Local Government. This Department is also devolving around £1.9m annual Bus Service Operators Grant funding to Lancashire County Council relating to the tendered bus services they support, to allow decisions to be taken locally on how that funding should be spent.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50617/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50617/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50617/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-05-12",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps are being taken to ensure that funding is made available to maintain bus services in rural areas of Lancashire.","false","Biography information for Mark Menzies","Fylde","Mark Menzies","198385"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50618","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-05-14","<p>It has not proved possible to respond to my hon. Friend in the time available before Prorogation.</p>","Havant","Mr David Willetts",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50618/answer","Biography information for Lord Willetts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50618/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50618/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-05-12","Manufacturing Industries: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps the Government is taking to encourage more women to pursue a career in advanced manufacturing.","false","Biography information for Mark Menzies","Fylde","Mark Menzies","198398"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50619","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p>The Department is working with a number of organisations including the Campaign to End Loneliness and the Royal Voluntary Service to promote ways to tackle loneliness and the Silverline who provide a helpline offering support to older people.</p><p>A measure of social isolation will be published this year as part of the Adult Social Care Outcomes Framework to raise visibility and to support local authorities to address the issue of social isolation in their local communities. This measure will be shared with the Public Health Outcomes Framework.</p><p>We are reforming social care and the Care Bill places more emphasis on prevention – preventing, reducing and delaying crisis, tackling loneliness and isolation is a key part of prevention.</p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50619/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50619/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50619/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-12","Older People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department is taking to tackle the impact of loneliness on the quality of life of elderly people.","false","Biography information for Mark Menzies","Fylde","Mark Menzies","198384"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50620","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p>Through the Mandate we have asked NHS England to make measurable progress towards making our health service among the best in Europe at supporting people with ongoing health problems, such as rheumatoid arthritis, to live healthily and independently, with much better control over the care they receive.</p><p> </p><p>In 2009, the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) published clinical guidance on the management of rheumatoid arthritis (RA) in adults, which set outs best practice on the diagnosis, care, treatment and support of patients. The guidance makes clear the importance of early diagnosis and is explicit that</p><p>suspected cases should be referred as an urgent priority for specialist assessment and that early initiation of treatment can prevent irreversible damage to joints.</p><p> </p><p>In addition to this, information on the diagnosis and treatment of RA can also be accessed via the NICE Clinical Knowledge summaries website at:</p><p> </p><p>http://cks.nice.org.uk/rheumatoid-arthritis</p><p> </p><p>More general information for the public can be found on the NHS Choices website at:</p><p> </p><p>www.nhs.uk/conditions/rheumatoid-arthritis</p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50620/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50620/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50620/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-12",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to improve the early intervention in and treatment for rheumatoid arthritis.","false","Biography information for Mark Menzies","Fylde","Mark Menzies","198399"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50621","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p><em>Improving Outcomes: A Strategy for Cancer</em>, published in January 2011, committed over £450 million over the four years up to 2014/15 to achieve earlier diagnosis of cancer. The earlier diagnosis money also included central funding for Be Clear on Cancer campaigns.</p><p> </p><p>The Department provided £2.5 million in 2010/11 to support 18 local awareness campaigns, including seven intended to raise awareness of breast cancer in women over 70. Lancashire and South Cumbria Cancer Network area was one of the pilot areas. In 2014, we funded a national campaign on breast cancer in women over 70 at a cost of around £2.2 million.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50621/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50621/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50621/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-12",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what funding his Department has made available in Lancashire to improve the early diagnosis of breast cancer.","false","Biography information for Mark Menzies","Fylde","Mark Menzies","198388"
