"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50493","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-05-14","<p> </p><p>I refer the hon. Member to my answer to the rt. hon. Member for Leeds Central (Hilary Benn), on 13 May 2014, <em>Official Report</em>, Column 535-536W.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50493/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50493/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50493/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-05-09",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will place in the Library research he has commissioned on the effect that turning off street lighting and relying on ambient lighting has on levels of crime.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","198326"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50288","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-05-13","<p>The Government committed in 2010 to reduce the UK's nuclear weapons stockpile by the mid 2020s, down to no more than 120 operationally available warheads and no more than 180 warheads. Nevertheless, the United Kingdom will retain a credible, continuous and effective minimum nuclear deterrent for as long as the global security situation makes that necessary. The 2010 Strategic Defence and Security Review sets out the Government's approach in more detail.</p>","Faversham and Mid Kent","Hugh Robertson",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50288/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugh Robertson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50288/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50288/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will set out the steps he plans to take to remove UK nuclear weapons from deployment and their subsequent destruction.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","198199"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50289","Department for International Development","false","2014-05-14","<p> </p><p>British aid is helping to educate 800,000 Nigerian children, including 600,000 girls, through a package of educational support to state governments in Nigeria. DFID also has an extensive portfolio of programmes helping Nigeria to provide long-term security for its citizens, particularly working to prevent violence against women and girls. For example, DFID's Nigeria Stability and Reconciliation Programme is already scaling up its work in Borno State, and my officials are currently investigating what further support we can offer both in terms of education and security programmes.</p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50289/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50289/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50289/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assistance her Department is offering to Nigeria for the promotion of education for women and girls in a safe environment.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","198261"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50290","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-05-14","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) estimates that there are approximately 20 000 British nationals living or working in Nigeria.</p><p>We offer advice to those resident in, or travelling to Nigeria, through FCO Travel Advice. This Travel Advice was updated in the week commencing 14 April, around the time of the abduction of the school girls, to ensure that it provided British nationals travelling to, or working in Nigeria, the best possible information and advice on the potential threats and dangers.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Mark Simmonds",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50290/answer","Biography information for Mark Simmonds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50290/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50290/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent estimate he has made of the number of UK nationals living or working in Nigeria; and whether his Department has issued any updated advice to them since the abduction of more than 200 Nigerian schoolgirls.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","198260"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50291","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-05-14","<p>The range of estimates for generation by source, as a proportion of the UK's total electricity demand in 2015, is as follows:</p><p> </p><p><strong>Proportion of UK electricity requirement met by different sources, 2015</strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Source</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Proportion of total electricity requirement (%)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Onshore wind</p></td><td><p>5.6–6.6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Offshore wind</p></td><td><p>3.4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Solar</p></td><td><p>1.3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Nuclear</p></td><td><p>16.5–16.7</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>These have been calculated using data derived from the annual update of energy and emissions projections:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/updated-energy-and-emissions-projections-2013" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/updated-energy-and-emissions-projections-2013</a>.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50291/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50291/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50291/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what estimate he has made of the proportion of the UK's energy requirement that will be generated by (a) onshore wind, (b) offshore wind, (c) solar and (d) nuclear energy sources by the end of 2015.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","198258"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50292","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-05-14","<p> </p><p>Information on tenants' satisfaction in relation to repairs and maintenance in local authority housing for England is reported in the English Housing Survey. The data collected since 2008/9, which cannot be broken down by local authority area, are as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p>Satisfied %</p></td><td><p>Dissatisfied %</p></td><td><p>Neither satisfied nor dissatisfied %</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008/9</p></td><td><p>63.7</p></td><td><p>28.9</p></td><td><p>7.4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009/10</p></td><td><p>65.1</p></td><td><p>25.3</p></td><td><p>9.5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>65.8</p></td><td><p>25.9</p></td><td><p>8.3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>65.6</p></td><td><p>25.0</p></td><td><p>9.4</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Data for 2012/13 are expected to be published in July 2014.</p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50292/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50292/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50292/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what information his Department holds on the average satisfaction rating given by tenants relating to maintenance service in public housing in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","198259"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50293","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-05-14","<p>The Government is leading a wide-ranging programme of events and activities to mark the First World War centenary. HMS Caroline, moored in Belfast, has received £13.2 million from the Heritage Lottery Fund to enable this veteran of the Battle of Jutland to open as a floating museum for the battle's centenary in 2016. Commemorative paving stones will be laid in the hometowns of Victoria Cross recipients born in Northern Ireland. The 14-18NOW cultural programme summer 2014 season includes events in both Belfast and Derry/Londonderry. There will be other First World War related activity as part of the wider decade of centenary commemorations in Ireland and Northern Ireland. At the same time, the Northern Ireland Centenary Committee is developing plans for a cross-community commemorative event at St Anne's Cathedral, Belfast which will complement UK Government events in Glasgow, Belgium and London on 4 August 2014. Jeffrey Donaldson, as Chair of the Northern Ireland Centenary Committee, is a member of the UK Government Advisory Group.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50293/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50293/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50293/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what plans the Government has to hold events in Northern Ireland to commemorate the centenary of the First World War.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","198257"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50294","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-05-13","<p>The FCO is currently unable to provide a detailed breakdown of all items damaged or destroyed by rioters at the British Embassy in Tehran in November 2011. Since visits to Tehran by UK officials recommenced on 3 December 2013 – after a gap of two years – it has only be possible to conduct preliminary assessments of the condition of the Embassy. A comprehensive assessment of the damage will require a detailed survey by a specialist. Planning is currently underway to conduct this survey as soon as is practical.</p>","Faversham and Mid Kent","Hugh Robertson",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50294/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugh Robertson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50294/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50294/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 6 May 2014, Official Report, column 72W, on Iran, if he will provide a detailed itemisation of works of art, antiquities, fixtures and fittings and other items of public property damaged or destroyed by rioters in HM Embassy in Tehran in 2011.","false","Biography information for Michael Ellis","Northampton North","Michael Ellis","198221"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50295","Department of Health","false","2014-05-13","<p>The aim of the Government's pay policy is to fairly reward nurses and other staff while ensuring that pay is affordable and that front-line patient services are protected. Our assessment of this policy is that it has been effective in recruiting, retaining and motivating the nursing workforce. There are now more nurses than at any time under the previous Government.</p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50295/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50295/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50295/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made the effect of recent NHS pay policy on the ability of the NHS to recruit and retain nursing staff.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","198270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50296","Department of Health","false","2014-05-13","<p>NHS England is currently planning to procure an agency to conduct research with the public and stakeholder groups to inform communications and engagement activity with those audiences for the care.data programme.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Should a contract be let which is in relation to, or in support of, care.data the procurement of those goods and/or services will be compliant with the Public Contracts Regulations 2006, as amended. Any procurement would be aligned with applicable government policies and shall ensure best practice is followed, including a robust evaluation of bidders against objective criteria.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50296/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50296/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50296/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 7 April 2014, Official Report, column 43W, on medical records: databases, whether his Department plans any procurement in connection with care.data.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","198271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50297","Department of Health","false","2014-05-13","<p>The Public Contracts Regulations 2006, as amended, allow for suppliers to be classed as ineligible to bid for contracts in circumstances where the supplier or its representative has been convicted of criminal offences relating to conspiracy, corruption, bribery or fraud. Where this is not the case, suppliers must be treated equally and track record would be assessed in line with government policy as part of any tendering process.</p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50297/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50297/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50297/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to his Answer of 13 March 2014, Official Report, column 355W, on medical records: databases, if he will bar ATOS from having any involvement with care.data.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","198272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50298","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-05-13","<p> </p><p>Forestry is a devolved matter. As far as public forests in England are concerned, I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 10 April 2014, Official Report, column 394W, to the hon. Member for Sterling (Anne McGuire).</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50298/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50298/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50298/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if he will bring forward legislative proposals to protect the UK's forests.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","198252"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50299","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-05-13","<p>The terms of the Deep and Comprehensive Free Trade Agreement are currently being negotiated between the EU and the Kingdom of Morocco. The agreement is between the European Communities and their Member States and the Kingdom of Morocco.</p>","Faversham and Mid Kent","Hugh Robertson",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50299/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugh Robertson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50299/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50299/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether the provisions of the EU Deep and Comprehensive Free trade Agreement with Morocco apply outside the sovereign territory of Morocco.","false","Biography information for Cathy Jamieson","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Cathy Jamieson","198209"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50300","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-05-13","<p>The UK does not regard any power as the de facto administrator of that part of the territory of Western Sahara not under Moroccan control.</p>","Faversham and Mid Kent","Hugh Robertson",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50300/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugh Robertson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50300/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50300/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, who the de facto administering power is in the area of Western Sahara not under Moroccan control; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Cathy Jamieson","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Cathy Jamieson","198207"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50301","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-05-13","<p> </p><p>The Secretary of State has met with the Indian High Commissioner to discuss the ban on imports of mangoes from India and will be working with the European Commission and other Member States to facilitate a lifting of the ban subject to the necessary plant health standards being achieved. Defra officials have discussed the issue with the main trade association, the Fresh Produce Consortium, both prior to and following the introduction of the ban and also recently with the National Asian Business Network.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50301/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50301/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50301/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what discussions, he has had with (a) EU officials, (b) Indian authorities and (c) affected UK businesses regarding the European Commission's ban on the import of Indian mangoes.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","198233"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50302","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-05-14","<p> </p><p>Protecting the UK's plants from incursions of pests and diseases is a high priority for the Government. There would be a major long term impact and costs from introducing more plant pests and diseases into the country. The pests intercepted on imports from India could cause significant damage to UK glasshouse crops worth £321 million a year. Such pests were found in 207 consignments of fruits and vegetables from India imported into the EU in 2013, of which 179 were intercepted by the UK.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>While a detailed assessment of the economic impact on UK businesses of the ban on the import of Indian mangoes has not been undertaken, the Government recognises the implications this will have and officials have met with the National Asian Business Association to discuss the issue.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We very much hope that imports of this highly-valued product will be able to resume as quickly as possible and will work with the European Commission and other Member States to facilitate this, subject to India's exporters and government showing that the necessary standards are being achieved.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50302/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50302/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50302/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if his Department has undertaken any assessment into the European Commission's ban on the import of Indian mangoes and the economic impact on UK businesses.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","198234"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50303","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-05-13","<p> </p><p>The Office of the Public Guardian (an executive agency of the Ministry of Justice) is piloting an assisted digital service through three third sector organisations: Alzheimer's Society, Age UK and CAB. Customers identified as requiring the service are signposted by the OPG contact centre to the providers national contact numbers. The pilots are being used to assess the extent of the assisted digital need and to evaluate different methods for delivery.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Before going live every digital by default service is required to make sure appropriate assisted digital support is in place. Services are working with GDS to understand who their assisted digital users are and what this support should look like.</p>","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Simon Hughes",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50303/answer","Biography information for Simon Hughes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50303/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50303/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the oral Answer of 30 April 2014, Official Report, column 815, how the assisted digital service for lasting power of attorney is provided and accessed; and what assisted digital services are in place for other Government digital services.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","198286"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50304","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-05-13","<p>The next phase of the Building Information Modelling (BIM) programme will include provision for data interaction between designs created using BIM and other interfaces, such as Smart Cities. The potential for this to give rise to security issues has been considered as part of the base design, and this phase will incorporate a secure but workable approach developed in conjunction with partners inside and outside of Government.</p>","Havant","Mr David Willetts",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50304/answer","Biography information for Lord Willetts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50304/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50304/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Answer of 10 April 2014, Official Report, column 312W, on building regulations, what assessment he has made of the cybersecurity implications of the Building Information Modelling Smart City project.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","198285"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50305","Women and Equalities","false","2014-05-13","<p>I have given no guidance to other departments on commissioning publicly-funded research into gender differences in brain development and functioning.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50305/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50305/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50305/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Ministers for Women and Equalities, what guidance she has given to other Departments on commissioning publicly-funded research into gender differences in brain development and functioning.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","198267"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50306","Department for Transport","false","2014-05-12","<p> </p><p>The Government intends to turn the Highways Agency (HA) into a government-owned Strategic Highways Company (SHC), as confirmed in the response to consultation published on 30th April. As announced by the Chief Secretary to the Treasury in June 2013, the new company will operate with guaranteed multi-year funding settlements and have the flexibility to move funds between years.</p><p> </p><p>As a company, outside of the civil service but inside the public sector, the SHC will have more autonomy over its internal governance arrangements and delivery processes so that it can respond to business needs more effectively.</p><p>The Government is continuing to work through the details of its relationship with the SHC to provide the necessary commercial freedom to boost delivery and improve efficiency, whilst ensuring value for money for the taxpayer.</p><p> </p><p>The rights of existing HA staff will be protected in accordance with TUPE principles.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50306/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50306/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50306/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what civil service restrictions will be removed should the Highways Agency be moved to a GoCO.","false","Biography information for John McDonnell","Hayes and Harlington","John McDonnell","198246"
