"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50378","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-05-14","<p>There is no such principle. In accordance with Treasury guidelines the Department is required to achieve best value for money in the sale of each site.<br><br>In the case of Kirton in Lindsey, following the aborted sale to the Homes and Communities Agency, the MOD decided to proceed straight to the open market. The department will be happy to receive a tender from North Lincolnshire District Council to be considered along with all other bids in fair and open competition.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50378/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50378/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50378/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50378/answer/previousversion/10134","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will ensure that North Lincolnshire Council has first refusal for the acquisition of the Kirtin in Lindsey base.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","198169"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50379","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-05-14","<p>There is no such principle. In accordance with Treasury guidelines the Department is required to achieve best value for money in the sale of each site.<br><br>In the case of Kirton in Lindsey, following the aborted sale to the Homes and Communities Agency, the MOD decided to proceed straight to the open market. The department will be happy to receive a tender from North Lincolnshire District Council to be considered along with all other bids in fair and open competition.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50379/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50379/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50379/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50379/answer/previousversion/10135","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will make it his policy to apply in all circumstances the Defence Infrastructure Organisation's principles that local councils should have first refusal when assets are being disposed of.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","198170"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50380","HM Treasury","false","2014-05-12","<p>I have done so.</p>","Loughborough","Nicky Morgan",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50380/answer","Biography information for Nicky Morgan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50380/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50380/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when he plans to respond to Question 193089, tabled on 20 March 2014 for answer on 25 March 2014.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","198277"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50382","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-05-13","<p>Conflict in northern Nigeria has caused great suffering in communities of different faiths and ethnicities. Representatives of The Government maintain regular contact with religious and ethnic community leaders across Nigeria. We recognise there are tensions in many parts of the country, including in the north east, middle belt and the Niger Delta. Recent attacks by Boko Haram have been indiscriminate, but it is almost certain that these attacks have killed more Muslims than Christians.</p><p>We recognise the underlying issues of poverty and inequality, which lead to inter-communal tensions and conflict in Nigeria and we urge political, traditional and religious leaders to work together in order to resolve these issues. The Department for International Development (DFID), the Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) and the Ministry of Defence (MOD) continue to fund a range of conflict resolution projects across Nigeria designed to address these problems. We currently have an expert team in Abuja to help Nigeria deal with the abduction of the school girls from Chibok and to also look at addressing longer term challenges, including inter-communal tensions.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Mark Simmonds",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50382/answer","Biography information for Mark Simmonds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50382/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50382/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment his Department has made of the situation for religious minorities in northern Nigeria.","false","Biography information for Chris Evans","Islwyn","Chris Evans","198231"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50383","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-05-13","<p>British officials regularly receive reports on a wide range of human rights issues, including the treatment of religious minorities in Burma. We share UN Special Rapporteur for Burma Tomas Ojea Quintana's concerns, as noted in his final report to the UN Human Rights Council on 2 April 2014, that the Burmese government is “not fulfilling its international human rights obligation to tackle incitement to violence based on national, racial or religious hatred”. We are particularly concerned by the rise in anti-Muslim attacks and hate speech over the last two years, continued intercommunal tensions in Rakhine State and the plight of the Rohingya. I raised our wider concerns about the situation in Rakhine State with senior Burmese Ministers during their visit in January and Baroness Warsi discussed the situation with the Burmese Minister of National Planning and Economic Development, Dr Kan Zaw, during his visit to the UK in March. During my visit to Burma in January, I also met the Kachin Baptist Convention, the largest religious organisation in Kachin State. We continue to encourage religious tolerance and dialogue and call on the Burmese authorities and community leaders to help create a conducive environment for this to take place.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50383/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50383/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50383/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent reports he has received on the situation for religious minorities in Burma.","false","Biography information for Chris Evans","Islwyn","Chris Evans","198232"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50384","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-05-13","<p>The ongoing crisis has clearly had a devastating impact on Christians, and on all of Syria's communities. We remain deeply concerned by the situation for Christian communities in Syria, including in Raqqah and Kessab.</p><p>This reinforces the need for us to support the moderate opposition who, as the UN Commission of Inquiry has acknowledged, have a pluralist and democratic vision for Syria and who are fighting extremist groups such as ISIL which pose a grave threat to Christians and others.</p>","Faversham and Mid Kent","Hugh Robertson",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50384/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugh Robertson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50384/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50384/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment his Department has made of the situation of Christian communities in Syria.","false","Biography information for Chris Evans","Islwyn","Chris Evans","198237"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50385","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p>A copy of West Midlands Ambulance Service NHS Foundation Trust (FT) system indicators performance data for 2012-13 has been placed in the Library.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The Department is aware that West Midlands Ambulance Service NHS FT met all three response time targets for the full year in 2012-13; despite a challenging winter period; a 6.9% rise in emergency calls; and a delay to the launch of the 111 system by NHS Direct in the West Midlands.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50385/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50385/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50385/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the West Midlands Ambulance Service's system's indicators performance in 2012-13; and what assessment he has made of the reasons for changes in that level of performance.","false","Biography information for Joan Walley","Stoke-on-Trent North","Joan Walley","198247"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50386","Department of Health","false","2014-05-13","<p /> <p /> <p> </p><p>The Chief Medical Officer for England has written twice (on 23 February 2012 and 22 November 2013) to all medical practitioners reminding them of their responsibilities under the Abortion Act.</p><p> </p><p>The Department will be providing further guidance to all those involved in providing abortion care on compliance with the Act; this will be published shortly.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50386/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50386/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50386/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when he last amended his Department's guidelines on the authorising of abortions; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","198255"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50387","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-05-14","<p>The Ministry of Defence, including military personnel, is participating in the UK Advisory Team drawn from across Whitehall, which has been sent to Nigeria to offer advice to the Nigerian authorities, including on longer-term counter-terrorism solutions to prevent such attacks in the future. I refer the hon. Member to the written statement released by my right hon. Friend the Foreign Secretary (William Hague), on 12 May 2014, (Official Report, column 15WS), and the comments he made in the House on 13 May 2014 (Official Report, column 579).</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50387/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50387/answer","Foreign and Commonwealth Office.doc WMS Nigeria Chibok Abductions.doc ; Nigeria.doc","Foreign and Commonwealth Office.doc WMS Nigeria Chibok Abductions.doc ; Nigeria.doc","WMS Attachment on Nigeria 12 May 2014 ; William Hague comments on Nigeria 13 May 2014","WMS Attachment on Nigeria 12 May 2014 ; William Hague comments on Nigeria 13 May 2014","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50387/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50387/answer/previousversion/10133","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the role is of UK military personnel in Nigeria in connection with the mass abduction of schoolgirls.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","198219"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50388","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p>The number of full-time equivalent staff (FTE) in the Department working on cancer policy for each of the past three years has been presented in the following table:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>FTE staff</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>18.3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>17.1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>16.7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>3.5</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Other Departmental staff work on related issues, such as cancer prevention, National Institute for Health and Care Excellence guidance and the Cancer Drugs Fund. From 1 April 2013, NHS England (rather than the Department) has been responsible for delivering improvements in all cancer services, with Public Health England (PHE) responsible for aspects of cancer screening, immunisation, prevention and symptom awareness.</p><p> </p><p>To reflect new structures, a number of posts were created in NHS England and PHE, taking on some of the responsibilities of the previous Departmental Cancer Policy team.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50388/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50388/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50388/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many full-time equivalent staff were employed to work on cancer policy in his Department in (a) 2010-11, (b) 2011-12, (c) 2012-13 and (d) 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Mr John Leech","Manchester, Withington","Mr John Leech","198265"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50389","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p>The information requested on staffing levels is not held centrally. Prior to 1 April 2013, staffing levels for both clinical networks, including cancer networks, and strategic health authorities, including staff working specifically in cancer networks, were a matter for local National Health Service organisations.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England does not employ people to work on disease-specific policy areas. It is structured according to five domains of the NHS Outcomes Framework. Only National Clinical Directors (NCD) are employed to work on specific conditions. There is one NCD for cancer employed on a 0.4 full-time equivalent basis. It is likely that most directorates will have roles contributing to improved outcomes for people with, and at risk of cancer, but NHS England does not record staff time in a way which would make this quantifiable.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","198197 ; 198198","2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50389/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50389/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50389/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many full-time equivalent staff were employed by NHS England to work on cancer policy at a national level in each of the last two years.","false","Biography information for Mr John Leech","Manchester, Withington","Mr John Leech","198266"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50390","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p>The information requested on staffing levels is not held centrally. Prior to 1 April 2013, staffing levels for both clinical networks, including cancer networks, and strategic health authorities, including staff working specifically in cancer networks, were a matter for local National Health Service organisations.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England does not employ people to work on disease-specific policy areas. It is structured according to five domains of the NHS Outcomes Framework. Only National Clinical Directors (NCD) are employed to work on specific conditions. There is one NCD for cancer employed on a 0.4 full-time equivalent basis. It is likely that most directorates will have roles contributing to improved outcomes for people with, and at risk of cancer, but NHS England does not record staff time in a way which would make this quantifiable.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","198198 ; 198266","2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50390/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50390/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50390/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many full-time equivalent staff were employed by strategic health authorities in (a) 2010-11, (b) 2011-12 and (c) 2012-13; and how many such staff worked specifically in cancer networks.","false","Biography information for Mr John Leech","Manchester, Withington","Mr John Leech","198197"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50391","Department of Health","false","2014-05-14","<p>The information requested on staffing levels is not held centrally. Prior to 1 April 2013, staffing levels for both clinical networks, including cancer networks, and strategic health authorities, including staff working specifically in cancer networks, were a matter for local National Health Service organisations.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England does not employ people to work on disease-specific policy areas. It is structured according to five domains of the NHS Outcomes Framework. Only National Clinical Directors (NCD) are employed to work on specific conditions. There is one NCD for cancer employed on a 0.4 full-time equivalent basis. It is likely that most directorates will have roles contributing to improved outcomes for people with, and at risk of cancer, but NHS England does not record staff time in a way which would make this quantifiable.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","198197 ; 198266","2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50391/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50391/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50391/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many full-time equivalent staff were employed by each of the 28 cancer networks in England in (a) 2010-11, (b) 2011-12 and (c) 2012-13.","false","Biography information for Mr John Leech","Manchester, Withington","Mr John Leech","198198"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50392","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-05-13","<p>None of the six requests for special mission status to which I referred in my answer to the House of 28 April 2014, Official Report, columns 594-5W, were refused. After consenting to the visits as special missions, two of the visits were subsequently cancelled by the country making the request. <br>As I noted in my previous answer, in view of the confidentiality of diplomatic exchanges, we have no plans to make public further details about requests that have been granted or refused. But if those applying for special mission status wish to announce the details of their visit to the UK, they are of course at liberty to do so.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Mark Simmonds","198229 ; 198230","2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50392/answer","Biography information for Mark Simmonds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50392/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50392/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-05-08",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answers of 28 April 2014, Official Report, columns 594-5W, on official visits, whether any of the six received requests for special mission status were refused (a) by reference to duties to prosecute or extradite persons alleged to have committed or to have ordered to be committed grave breaches of the Fourth Geneva Convention or other international crimes and (b) on other human rights grounds.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Mr Andy Slaughter","198228"
