"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50190","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-05-14","<p> </p><p> </p><p>The latest records for the number of magistrates that sat for more than 70 half days are for 2012/13. 759 magistrates sat for more than 70 half days in that year. It may also assist if I explain that 244 of those magistrates sat on panels, such as youth, family and fine enforcement.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50190/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50190/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50190/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-05-07",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many magistrates sat more than 70 half days in the last year.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","198010"
