"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50198","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-05-12","<p /> <p /> <p>The potential implications of closing the Independent Living Fund are set out clearly in the Equality Analysis that was published on 6 March alongside the Written Ministerial Statement announcing the closure.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50198/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50198/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50198/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-05-07",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the number of recipients of the Independent Living Fund who will move into residential care following closure of the Fund.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","198017"
